📦 Patch Plan (Planned Changes)

Overview

This patch introduces major improvements in:

- Security
- Sync reliability
- Extension source handling
- Public sharing safety
- Performance (diff-based sync)
- User transparency (logs & preview)

---

🔐 Security Improvements

1. Public Gist Sanitization

- Public gist no longer uploads raw settings
- Sensitive values are automatically removed:
  - tokens, API keys, passwords, auth, cookies, etc.
- Antigravity configs ("mcp_config.json", "browserAllowlist.txt") are excluded

2. Extension Install Safety

- Extension install/remove now requires user confirmation
- Prevents malicious or unintended remote execution

3. Trust Model

Gists are classified into:

- "self"
- "trusted"
- "untrusted"

Restrictions:

- External gist cannot auto-install extensions
- Limited sync behavior for untrusted sources

---

🔄 Sync Behavior Changes

4. Manual Sync Mode (Default)

- Auto sync disabled by default
- User must explicitly trigger:
  - Upload
  - Download

5. Extension Sync Fix

- Prevent reinstall loop after extension removal
- Sync no longer runs automatically on restart

---

📊 Diff & Change Detection

6. Diff-based Sync Engine

- Only changed data is applied
- Avoids full overwrite

7. Sync Preview

Before applying changes:

- Settings changes
- Extension additions/removals
- Snippet updates

---

⚡ Performance Optimization

8. Skip Unchanged Data

- Compare local vs remote before applying
- Skip identical content

9. Sync Manifest

New file:

sync-manifest.json

Contains:

- version
- hashes
- changed files

---

🧠 Partial Sync (Index-based)

10. Change Index

New file:

sync-index.json

Tracks:

- changed paths
- extension actions

Used for:

- faster apply
- selective updates

---

🕘 History + Diff

11. History Diff View

- Show what changed per revision
- Not just timestamp

Example:

- settings: 3 changed
- extensions: +1 / -2

12. Restore Preview

Before restoring:

- show diff
- confirm action

---

📜 Logging System

13. Sync Logs

Track:

- operation (upload/download/restore)
- applied changes
- skipped items
- errors

14. Output Channel

- Display logs in VS Code output
- Optional local history storage

---

🌐 Custom Marketplace Support

15. Custom Marketplace

- User-defined marketplace support
- Used as fallback after:
  - VS Code Marketplace
  - Open VSX

---

❓ Unknown Extensions Handling

16. Unknown Extensions

If not found in marketplaces:

- Provide install URL
- Add custom marketplace
- Ignore

---

🧩 Public Share Mode

17. Public Share Profile

- Separate from private backup
- Only safe settings included:
  - editor config
  - extension list
  - snippets

---

🏁 Summary

This patch evolves the extension from:

«a simple settings sync tool»

into:

«a secure, controllable, and transparent environment sync system»

---

